  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Upstream and Downstream Filtering</title>\n<style>\n* {\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 0;\n}\n\nbody {\n  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n  background: #0a0a0a;\n  color: #e0e0e0;\n  padding: 20px;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n}\n\n.container {\n  max-width: 800px;\n  margin: 0 auto;\n}\n\nh1 {\n  font-size: 1.8rem;\n  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\n  color: #ffffff;\n  font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n.concept {\n  font-size: 1rem;\n  color: #a0a0a0;\n  margin-bottom: 2rem;\n  line-height: 1.5;\n}\n\n.lab-container {\n  background: #1a1a1a;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  padding: 2rem;\n  margin-bottom: 2rem;\n}\n\n.controls {\n  margin-bottom: 2rem;\n}\n\n.control-group {\n  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\n}\n\nlabel {\n  display: block;\n  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\n  font-weight: 500;\n  color: #ffffff;\n}\n\n.slider-container {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  gap: 1rem;\n}\n\ninput[type=\"range\"] {\n  flex: 1;\n  height: 6px;\n  border-radius: 3px;\n  background: #333;\n  outline: none;\n  -webkit-appearance: none;\n}\n\ninput[type=\"range\"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {\n  -webkit-appearance: none;\n  width: 18px;\n  height: 18px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  background: #4a9eff;\n  cursor: pointer;\n}\n\ninput[type=\"range\"]::-moz-range-thumb {\n  width: 18px;\n  height: 18px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  background: #4a9eff;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  border: none;\n}\n\n.value-display {\n  min-width: 80px;\n  text-align: right;\n  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n  color: #4a9eff;\n}\n\n.filter-toggle {\n  display: flex;\n  gap: 1rem;\n  margin-top: 0.5rem;\n}\n\n.toggle-btn {\n  flex: 1;\n  padding: 0.75rem;\n  border: 2px solid #333;\n  background: #1a1a1a;\n  color: #e0e0e0;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  font-size: 0.95rem;\n  transition: all 0.2s;\n}\n\n.toggle-btn.active {\n  background: #2a4a6a;\n  border-color: #4a9eff;\n  color: #ffffff;\n}\n\n.toggle-btn:hover {\n  border-color: #4a9eff;\n}\n\n.visualization {\n  position: relative;\n  height: 400px;\n  background: #0f0f0f;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\n}\n\ncanvas {\n  display: block;\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 100%;\n}\n\n.stats {\n  display: grid;\n  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));\n  gap: 1rem;\n  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\n}\n\n.stat-box {\n  background: #0f0f0f;\n  padding: 1rem;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  border-left: 3px solid #4a9eff;\n}\n\n.stat-label {\n  font-size: 0.85rem;\n  color: #808080;\n  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;\n}\n\n.stat-value {\n  font-size: 1.5rem;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  color: #ffffff;\n  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n}\n\n.stat-value.warning {\n  color: #ff6b6b;\n}\n\n.stat-value.good {\n  color: #51cf66;\n}\n\n.explanation {\n  background: #0f0f0f;\n  padding: 1.5rem;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  border-left: 3px solid #4a9eff;\n  color: #b0b0b0;\n  font-size: 0.95rem;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n}\n\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n  body {\n    padding: 15px;\n  }\n  \n  h1 {\n    font-size: 1.5rem;\n  }\n  \n  .lab-container {\n    padding: 1.5rem;\n  }\n  \n  .stats {\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n  }\n}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <h1>Upstream and Downstream Filtering</h1>\n  <p class=\"concept\">A quality-control system can filter at entry or filter after entry by removing bad items later—when production cost drops to near-zero, the second strategy fails because pollution arrives faster than the system can clean, forcing a shift to stricter gates at submission.</p>\n  \n  <div class=\"lab-container\">\n    <div class=\"controls\">\n      <div class=\"control-group\">\n        <label>Filter strategy</label>\n        <div class=\"filter-toggle\">\n          <button class=\"toggle-btn active\" data-mode=\"downstream\">Clean up later</button>\n          <button class=\"toggle-btn\" data-mode=\"upstream\">Block at entry</button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      \n      <div class=\"control-group\">\n        <label>Production cost per bad submission</label>\n        <div class=\"slider-container\">\n          <input type=\"range\" id=\"costSlider\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"80\" step=\"1\">\n          <span class=\"value-display\" id=\"costValue\">80 hours</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      \n      <div class=\"control-group\">\n        <label>Cleanup capacity (bad items removed per day)</label>\n        <div class=\"slider-container\">\n          <input type=\"range\" id=\"cleanupSlider\" min=\"5\" max=\"50\" value=\"20\" step=\"1\">\n          <span class=\"value-display\" id=\"cleanupValue\">20 / day</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"stats\">\n      <div class=\"stat-box\">\n        <div class=\"stat-label\">Bad submissions per day</div>\n        <div class=\"stat-value\" id=\"submissionRate\">12</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"stat-box\">\n        <div class=\"stat-label\">Items in system</div>\n        <div class=\"stat-value\" id=\"systemLoad\">85</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"stat-box\">\n        <div class=\"stat-label\">System state</div>\n        <div class=\"stat-value good\" id=\"systemState\">Stable</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"visualization\">\n      <canvas id=\"canvas\"></canvas>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"explanation\" id=\"explanation\">\n      When production cost is high, bad submissions arrive slowly. A system that cleans up after entry can keep up—pollution never accumulates. As cost drops toward zero, production accelerates. At some point, bad items flood in faster than the system can remove them. The queue grows without bound. The only fix is to reject more at entry, before pollution enters the system.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\nconst costSlider = document.getElementById('costSlider');\nconst cleanupSlider = document.getElementById('cleanupSlider');\nconst costValue = document.getElementById('costValue');\nconst cleanupValue = document.getElementById('cleanupValue');\nconst submissionRate = document.getElementById('submissionRate');\nconst systemLoad = document.getElementById('systemLoad');\nconst systemState = document.getElementById('systemState');\nconst explanation = document.getElementById('explanation');\nconst toggleBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.toggle-btn');\n\nlet mode = 'downstream'; // 'downstream' or 'upstream'\nlet cost = 80;\nlet cleanupCapacity = 20;\nlet items = [];\nlet timeStep = 0;\nlet accumulatedTime = 0;\nlet hasEngaged = false;\n\nfunction resizeCanvas() {\n  const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();\n  canvas.width = rect.width * window.devicePixelRatio;\n  canvas.height = rect.height * window.devicePixelRatio;\n  ctx.scale(window.devicePixelRatio, window.devicePixelRatio);\n}\n\nwindow.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\nresizeCanvas();\n\nfunction costToRate(c) {\n  // High cost (100) → ~2/day, Low cost (0) → ~500/day\n  // Exponential curve\n  return Math.round(2 + 498 * Math.pow((100 - c) / 100, 2));\n}\n\nfunction updateStats() {\n  const rate = costToRate(cost);\n  submissionRate.textContent = rate;\n  systemLoad.textContent = items.length;\n  \n  let state = 'Stable';\n  let stateClass = 'good';\n  \n  if (mode === 'downstream') {\n    if (rate > cleanupCapacity) {\n      state = 'Overload';\n      stateClass = 'warning';\n    }\n  } else {\n    // Upstream blocks most, only ~5% get through\n    const throughput = Math.max(1, Math.round(rate * 0.05));\n    if (throughput > cleanupCapacity) {\n      state = 'Overload';\n      stateClass = 'warning';\n    }\n  }\n  \n  systemState.textContent = state;\n  systemState.className = 'stat-value ' + stateClass;\n}\n\nfunction updateExplanation() {\n  const rate = costToRate(cost);\n  \n  if (mode === 'downstream') {\n    if (cost > 50) {\n      explanation.textContent = 'High production cost means bad submissions arrive slowly. The cleanup crew can handle them. The system stays clean without blocking anyone at entry.';\n    } else if (rate <= cleanupCapacity) {\n      explanation.textContent = 'Production cost dropped, but cleanup capacity still matches the flow. The system works, but it\\'s near the edge. A small increase in bad submissions would break it.';\n    } else {\n      explanation.textContent = 'Production cost hit near-zero. Bad submissions flood in faster than the cleanup crew can remove them. The queue grows without bound. Pollution spreads before removal. Filtering after entry cannot keep up.';\n    }\n  } else {\n    if (cost > 50) {\n      explanation.textContent = 'With strict entry gates, most bad submissions are rejected before they enter. The small number that slip through are easily cleaned up. The system stays stable, but every submission faces scrutiny.';\n    } else {\n      explanation.textContent = 'Even with near-zero production cost, upstream filtering blocks most bad submissions at the gate. Only a fraction enter the system. Cleanup capacity handles them easily. The trade-off: every submitter faces a gate check.';\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nfunction addItem() {\n  const rate = costToRate(cost);\n  const interval = mode === 'downstream' ? (1 / rate) : (1 / Math.max(1, rate * 0.05));\n  \n  accumulatedTime += 1/60; // 60fps\n  \n  while (accumulatedTime >= interval) {\n    accumulatedTime -= interval;\n    items.push({\n      x: Math.random() * (canvas.width / window.devicePixelRatio - 20) + 10,\n      y: -10,\n      vy: 0.5 + Math.random() * 0.5,\n      size: 4 + Math.random() * 3,\n      alpha: 1\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction removeItems() {\n  // Remove up to cleanupCapacity items per day\n  // In animation time, remove proportionally each frame\n  const removalRate = cleanupCapacity / (60 * 60); // per frame (assuming 60fps, ~60 seconds = 1 day in sim)\n  \n  let toRemove = Math.floor(removalRate + Math.random());\n  \n  while (toRemove > 0 && items.length > 0) {\n    items.shift();\n    toRemove--;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction draw() {\n  const w = canvas.width / window.devicePixelRatio;\n  const h = canvas.height / window.devicePixelRatio;\n  \n  ctx.fillStyle = '#0f0f0f';\n  ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);\n  \n  // Update items\n  for (let i = items.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {\n    const item = items[i];\n    item.y += item.vy;\n    \n    if (item.y > h + 10) {\n      items.splice(i, 1);\n      continue;\n    }\n    \n    // Draw item\n    ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(255, 107, 107, ${item.alpha})`;\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.arc(item.x, item.y, item.size, 0, Math.PI * 2);\n    ctx.fill();\n  }\n  \n  // Draw filter line\n  if (mode === 'upstream') {\n    ctx.strokeStyle = '#4a9eff';\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\n    ctx.setLineDash([5, 5]);\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.moveTo(0, 30);\n    ctx.lineTo(w, 30);\n    ctx.stroke();\n    ctx.setLineDash([]);\n    \n    ctx.fillStyle = '#4a9eff';\n    ctx.font = '12px sans-serif';\n    ctx.fillText('Entry gate', 10, 25);\n  }\n  \n  addItem();\n  removeItems();\n  updateStats();\n  \n  timeStep++;\n  requestAnimationFrame(draw);\n}\n\ncostSlider.addEventListener('input', (e) => {\n  if (!hasEngaged) {\n    hasEngaged = true;\n    if (window.parent) {\n      window.parent.postMessage({type: 'interactive_engagement', event: 'manipulated'}, '*');\n    }\n  }\n  cost = parseInt(e.target.value);\n  costValue.textContent = cost === 0 ? '~0 hours' : `${cost} hours`;\n  updateExplanation();\n});\n\ncleanupSlider.addEventListener('input', (e) => {\n  if (!hasEngaged) {\n    hasEngaged = true;\n    if (window.parent) {\n      window.parent.postMessage({type: 'interactive_engagement', event: 'manipulated'}, '*');\n    }\n  }\n  cleanupCapacity = parseInt(e.target.value);\n  cleanupValue.textContent = `${cleanupCapacity} / day`;\n  updateExplanation();\n});\n\ntoggleBtns.forEach(btn => {\n  btn.addEventListener('click', (e) => {\n    if (!hasEngaged) {\n      hasEngaged = true;\n      if (window.parent) {\n        window.parent.postMessage({type: 'interactive_engagement', event: 'manipulated'}, '*');\n      }\n    }\n    toggleBtns.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));\n    btn.classList.add('active');\n    mode = btn.dataset.mode;\n    items = []; // Clear on mode change\n    updateExplanation();\n  });\n});\n\nupdateExplanation();\ndraw();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
